A25: ( m1 div d1 ) <> ( 0 ) by A1,A19;
(for x holds ((( ( ( a * x ) - c1 ) mod m1 ) = ( 0 ) & ( ( ( b * x ) - c2 ) mod m2 ) = ( 0 )) implies x,( r + ( ( m1 div ( a gcd m1 ) ) * w ) ) are_congruent_mod ( ( m1 div ( a gcd m1 ) ) * ( m2 div ( b gcd m2 ) ) )))
proof
